parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine mounts can cause excessive engine vibration, leading to premature wear on engine components, reduced vehicle performance, and potential engine damage.
Difficulty starting the engine in cold temperatures can lead to increased wear on the starter motor and battery, and may cause inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: engine "miss" that improves as engine warms up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the speed control system can cause unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Engine speed increases by 5-8 mph when signaling a lane change with speed control on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Radiator failure can cause engine overheating, leading to premature wear on engine components, reduced vehicle performance, and potential engine damage.
Lifter failure can cause engine noise, reduced engine performance, and potential engine damage.
Head gasket failure can cause engine coolant or oil leaks, leading to engine overheating, reduced engine performance, and potential engine damage.
Sudden brake failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: vehicle takes longer than usual to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents, especially if the vehicle is in motion or in a hazardous location.
symptoms: the battery is not holding a charge
the vehicle stalls or dies while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension components, including the sway bar and struts, can cause loss of vehicle control, reduced stability, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving
the vehicle leans or tilts while turning
the vehicle has uneven tire wear
the vehicle has a rough or bumpy ride.
